cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence algorithms and signal processing, which are common topics in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories. The use of electro-optical systems and delay-coupled architectures suggests a focus on cs.ET (Embedded Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. Finally, the use of the backpropagation algorithm and the evaluation of error rates suggests a focus on cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
